<div id="review_2377470964" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2377470964" />
    <a title="Luffy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7407364-luffy"><img alt="Luffy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1630342388p2/7407364.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2377470964?book_show_action=true">May 06, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luffy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luffy" href="/user/show/7407364-luffy">Luffy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780062430243" href="/book/show/33199875-the-good-daughter">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2377470964" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15479074332521461744">What did I think? I thought that the book was written very compactly. There was little breathing space. Usually I groan somewhat when reading two timelines. Not with this author.<br/><br/>Charlotte and Samantha Quinn are mere kids when they encounter a violent encounter. But now Charlotte herself is faced with going back in time to guess what happened actually.<br/><br/>This book has unambitious goals. To shock and excite maybe. But it is also a testament to the talent of the author, to keep her demanding readers g</span>
  <span id="freeText15479074332521461744" style="display:none">What did I think? I thought that the book was written very compactly. There was little breathing space. Usually I groan somewhat when reading two timelines. Not with this author.<br /><br />Charlotte and Samantha Quinn are mere kids when they encounter a violent encounter. But now Charlotte herself is faced with going back in time to guess what happened actually.<br /><br />This book has unambitious goals. To shock and excite maybe. But it is also a testament to the talent of the author, to keep her demanding readers guessing. And in the end, doesn't all art have twists and turns? I do recommend this book. It's well worth reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15479074332521461744" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
