              <span id="reviewTextContainer3050247555" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8283290658233273549">this DRAGGED from the end of the prologue until the last few chapters, but i have to give karin slaughter props for still managing to write something that can get under my skin after pretty girls. <br/><br/>a couple things to note:<br/><br/>decide for yourself if this one&apos;s right for you, as it is extremely dark. big warnings for graphic depictions of rape, violence, murder, miscarriages, loss of a loved one from cancer, and gun violence.<br/><br/>also idk who&apos;s behind trying to make this out to be the first book of a series</span>
  <span id="freeText8283290658233273549" style="display:none">this DRAGGED from the end of the prologue until the last few chapters, but i have to give karin slaughter props for still managing to write something that can get under my skin after pretty girls. <br /><br />a couple things to note:<br /><br />decide for yourself if this one's right for you, as it is extremely dark. big warnings for graphic depictions of rape, violence, murder, miscarriages, loss of a loved one from cancer, and gun violence.<br /><br />also idk who's behind trying to make this out to be the first book of a series, but it's a standalone with a novella companion that is not necessary to read unless you want the extra content.<br /></span>
